  Original BPMN request text:
  1. Start when the user decides to make toast. 2. Check whether bread is available. 3. If there is no bread, notify the user that toast cannot be made, then end the process. 4. If bread is available, take two slices of bread. 5. Set the toaster to a medium browning level and place the bread slices into the toaster. 6. Start the toaster. 7. Wait until the toaster finishes. 8. Remove the toast from the toaster. 9. Check whether the toast is burned. 10. If the toast is burned, discard it. If more bread is available, restart from step 4; otherwise end the process. 11. If the toast is not burned, place it on a plate. 12. Ask the user whether butter is desired. 13. If butter is desired, spread butter on the toast. 14. Serve the toast to the user. 15. The process ends successfully.
